y%2Fdelhi%2Fdelhi-excise-policy-case-arvind-kejriwal-court-order-ed-sommons-money-laundering%2Farticleshow%2F108539791.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Court%20Deference%20and%20Opposition%20Indifference%20May%20Allow%20CAA%20Push%20to%20Entrench%20Hindu%20Majoritarianism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15224742%2FCAA-support-II.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20now%2C%20as%20one%20enters%20into%20another%20national%20election%20season%2C%20there%20is%20little%20doubt%20in%20realising%20that%20the%20incumbent%20BJP%20government%20has%20created%20a%20formulaic%20approach%20to%20triggering%20chaos%20for%20electoral%20gains%20either%20through%20direct%20action%20or%20in%20letting%20chaotic%20events%20take%20their%20course%20for%20an%20exercise%20of%20post-event%20politicisation%20(during%20elections).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%202019%2C%20there%20was%20the%20Pulwama%20attack%20that%20occurred%20close%20to%20a%20national%20election%2C%20in%20the%20run%20up%20to%20which%20the%20BJP%20employed%20images%20of%20%E2%80%98martyred%E2%80%99%20soldiers%20while%20harnessing%20the%20popular%20vote%20for%20its%20rhetorical%20pitch%20of%20%E2%80%98nationalism%E2%80%99%20across%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPost-elections%2C%20one%20saw%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)-National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%20combine%20(explained%20by%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%E2%80%99s%20own%20%E2%80%98chronology%E2%80%99)%2C%20triggering%20nationwide%20protests%2C%20only%20to%20be%20quelled%20down%20by%20the%20nature%20of%20strict%20(curfew-style)%20lockdown%20measures%20introduced%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20scare%20(in%20late%202019%20and%20early%202020).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20street%20protests%20at%20the%20time%20across%20Indian%20cities%20and%20states%20were%20anchored%20not%20by%20politicians%20but%20angered%20youth%2C%20women%20and%20civil%20society%20groups%2C%20who%20found%20solace%20in%20peacefully%20protesting%20against%20the%20government%20by%20reading%20the%20constitution%E2%80%99s%20preamble%20and%20fighting%20discrimination%20meted%20against%20any%20religious%20minority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20as%20we%20walk%20into%20another%20national%20election%2C%20with%20a%20political%20opposition%20distraught%20and%20lacking%20a%20cohesive%20counter-electoral%20strategy%20to%20contest%20against%20the%20incumbent%20BJP%2C%20the%20home%20minister%20has%20once%20again%20brought%20the%20CAA%20(-NRC)%20chronology%20back%20into%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Tuesday%2C%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%20released%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleasePage.aspx%3FPRID%3D2013858%5C%22%3Ea%20list%20of%20questions%20and%20answers%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20an%20attempt%20to%20also%20respond%20to%20any%20%E2%80%98allegations%E2%80%99%20about%20the%20discriminatory%20nature%20of%20the%20CAA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20argued%20here%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20editor%2C%20Siddharth%20Varadarajan%2C%20this%20document%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhome-ministrys-positive-narrative-on-caa-is-full-of-lies-half-truths-and-really-bad-drafting%5C%22%3Efull%20of%20%E2%80%9Chalf-truths%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Coutright%20lies%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F3nwDRPXfVbg%3Fsi%3DhSNriocvu-471Zwe%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20agenda%20of%20the%20legislation%20is%20very%20clear.%20The%20BJP%20wants%20to%20use%20the%20CAA%20(and%20then%20the%20NRC)%20as%20a%20legalised%20force%20to%20change%20the%20macro-demographic%20composition%20across%20states%20in%20establishing%20a%20Hindu-majoritarian%20state%20while%20directly%20discriminating%20against%20religious%20minorities%20and%20Muslims%20in%20particular.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20principal%20concern%20here%20has%20little%20to%20do%20with%20(or%20say%20on)%20analysing%20the%20motivation%20or%20ideological%20agenda%20of%20a%20political%20party%20in%20power%20%E2%80%93%20which%20seems%20explicitly%20clear%20by%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20isn%E2%80%99t%20clear%2C%20though%2C%20is%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20judiciary%20and%20the%20apex%20court%20in%20particular%20have%20chosen%20to%20%3Cem%3Edeflect%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Edefer%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20their%20own%20role%20and%20responsibilities%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20sharing%20their%20views%20on%20a%20law%20some%20say%20is%20highly%20unconstitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EInterpreting%20the%20%E2%80%98constitutionality%E2%80%99%20test%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAA%20is%20under%20challenge%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20In%20December%202019%2C%20parliament%20amended%20the%201955%20Citizenship%20Act%20to%20grant%20citizenship%20to%20Hindu%2C%20Sikh%2C%20Buddhist%2C%20Jain%2C%20Parsi%20and%20Christian%20migrants%20who%20entered%20India%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20or%20Bangladesh%20before%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Union%20Muslim%20League%20(IUML)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-law%2Fcaa-issues-in-the-legal-challenge-to-the-law-9208839%5C%22%3Echallenged%20the%20amendment%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20which%20more%20than%20200%20petitions%20have%20been%20filed%20and%20tagged%20with%20the%20IUML%E2%80%99s%20challenge%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20report%20added%20that%20petitioners%20include%20Asaduddin%20Owaisi%2C%20Jairam%20Ramesh%2C%20Ramesh%20Chenninthala%20and%20Mahua%20Moitra%2C%20as%20well%20as%20political%20organisations%20such%20as%20the%20Assam%20Pradesh%20Congress%20Committee%2C%20the%20Asom%20Gana%20Parishad%2C%20the%20National%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20(Assam)%2C%20the%20Muslim%20Students%E2%80%99%20Federation%20(Assam)%20and%20the%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202022%2C%20a%20bench%20of%20the%20top%20court%20ordered%20that%20final%20hearings%20would%20begin%20in%20December%20that%20year%20after%20then-Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20U.U.%20Lait%E2%80%99s%20retirement%2C%20but%20the%20case%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20heard%20since%20then%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EExpress%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20website%20says%20the%20case%20is%20listed%20before%20a%20bench%20headed%20by%20Justice%20Pankaj%20Mithal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Funderstanding-caa-rules-the-process-and-what-it-means-to-resist%5C%22%3EUnderstanding%20CAA%20Rules%2C%20the%20Process%2C%20and%20What%20It%20Means%20to%20Resist%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20rely%20here%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2020%2F01%2F21%2Fthe-citizenship-amendment-act-challenge-three-ideas%2F%5C%22%3Ereviewing%20Gautam%20Bhatia%E2%80%99s%20legal%20reasoning%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20jurisprudential%20grounds%20challenging%20the%20CAA%E2%80%99s%20constitutionality%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20constitutional%20debate%20around%20the%20Citizenship%20(Amendment)%20Act%20has%20been%20framed%20around%20the%20following%20arguments%3A%20(a)%20does%20the%20grant%20of%20immunity%20and%20citizenship%20to%20a%20select%20group%20of%20migrants%20violate%20the%20principle%20of%20%E2%80%9Creasonable%20classification%E2%80%9D%20under%20Article%2014%2C%20by%20virtue%20of%20the%20individuals%20and%20groups%20it%20excludes%3F%3B%20(b)%20does%20the%20selection%20of%20groups%20lack%20any%20%E2%80%9Cdetermining%20principle%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20is%20therefore%20unconstitutionally%20arbitrary%3F%3B%20and%20(c)%20by%20privileging%20religious%20persecution%20over%20other%20forms%20of%20persecution%20in%20claims%20to%20citizenship%2C%20does%20the%20CAA%20violate%20the%20basic%20feature%20of%20%E2%80%9Csecularism%E2%80%9D%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20well-identified%20legal%20issues%20that%20come%20up%20in%20the%20constitutional%20challenge%20against%20the%20CAA%20for%20the%20courts%20to%20dwell%20upon.%20Bhatia%20also%20states%3A%20%E2%80%9CBeyond%20reasonable%20classification%2C%20arbitrariness%2C%20and%20secularism%2C%20there%20are%20deeper%20reasons%20to%20hold%20CAA%20unconstitutional.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2020%2F01%2F21%2Fthe-citizenship-amendment-act-challenge-three-ideas%2F%5C%22%3Eexplains%20these%20deeper%20reasons%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20three%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20according%20to%20him%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20principle%20of%20equality%20under%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20has%20moved%20beyond%20the%20%3Cem%3Eclassification%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3Earbitrariness%20%3C%2Fem%3Etests%3B%20%3Cem%3Esecondly%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20%E2%80%93%20contrary%20to%20a%20widespread%20assumption%20in%20our%20legal%20culture%20%E2%80%93%20citizenship%20laws%20deserve%C2%A0%3Cem%3Egreater%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Ejudicial%20scrutiny%20instead%20of%20%3Cstrong%3Ejudicial%20deference%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3B%20and%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ethirdly%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20that%20notwithstanding%20the%20language%20of%20Article%2011%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20there%20exist%20implied%20limitations%20upon%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20confer%20or%20withdraw%20citizenship%20%E2%80%93%20limitations%20that%20flow%20from%20the%20existence%20of%20equally%20important%20and%20fundamental%20constitutional%20principles.%E2%80%9D%20(emphasis%20in%20bold%20provided)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20role%20as%20a%20%3Cem%3Ecounter-majoritarian%3C%2Fem%3E%20institution%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20of%20judicial%20deference%20is%20an%20important%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20what%20is%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20here%20or%20what%20is%20the%20basic%20role%20of%20judicial%20review%20in%20a%20democratic%20society%3F%20For%20the%20answer%20to%20these%20questions%2C%20Bhatia%20drew%20from%20his%20reasoning%20justifying%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20interventive%20role%20(in%20terms%20of%20reviewing%20a%20law)%20as%20a%20counter-majoritarian%20institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20exists%20to%20check%20the%20%E2%80%9Cexcesses%20of%20majoritarianism%20on%20the%20understanding%20that%20true%20democracy%20meant%20something%20more%20than%20the%20brute%20majority%20rule%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F02%2F21031032%2F800px-Building_of_The_Supreme_Court_of_India.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-226122%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EFor%20now%2C%20the%20court%20appears%2C%20sadly%2C%20to%20be%20subjugated%20in%20agency%20and%20form.%20Credit%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FPinakpani.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20evolving%20constitutional%20idea%20of%20%E2%80%98equality%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findconlawphil.wordpress.com%2F2020%2F01%2F21%2Fthe-citizenship-amendment-act-challenge-three-ideas%2F%5C%22%3Ewas%20borrowed%20heavily%20from%20American%20jurisprudence%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20checking%20the%20excesses%20of%20majoritarianism%2C%20refer%20to%20this%20explanation%20by%20Bhatia%20offered%20here%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20its%20famous%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FUnited_States_v._Carolene_Products_Co.%23Footnote_Four%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ECarolene%20Products%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Efootnote%2C%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20noted%20that%20the%20role%20of%20the%20Court%20was%20particularly%20important%20in%20cases%20involving%20%E2%80%9Cdiscrete%20and%20insular%20minorities%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%3F%20Because%20it%20were%20these%20minorities%20that%20faced%20the%20greatest%20difficulties%20in%20articulating%20their%20interests%20through%20the%20normal%20channels%20of%20(majoritarian)%20democratic%20governance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20task%20of%20the%20Court%2C%20essentially%2C%20was%20to%20come%20to%20the%20rescue%20of%20those%20whom%20the%20political%20process%20%E2%80%93%20formally%20or%20effectively%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eexcluded%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0from%20equal%20participation.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20(emphasis%20in%20bold%20provided)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20if%20there%20is%20a%20country%20where%20same-sex%20relations%20are%20viewed%20with%20opprobrium%20by%20a%20large%20segment%20of%20the%20population%20%E2%80%93%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20the%20LGBTQ%2B%20community%20is%20permanently%20excluded%20from%20access%20to%20political%20power%2C%20as%20nobody%20else%20will%20ally%20with%20them%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Court%20is%20justified%20in%20subjecting%20laws%20targeting%20that%20community%20to%20stringent%20scrutiny.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20constitutional%20democracy%2C%20it%20is%20difficult%20for%20any%20one%20institution%20or%20branch%20of%20government%20to%20exercise%20%E2%80%98absolute%20power%E2%80%99.%20Even%20though%20Article%2011%20of%20the%20constitution%20gives%20parliament%20the%20right%20to%20%E2%80%9Cregulate%20citizenship%20by%20law%E2%80%9D%20and%20make%20%E2%80%9Cany%20provision%20with%20respect%20to%20acquisition%20and%20termination%20of%20citizenship%E2%80%9D%20as%20well%20as%20%E2%80%9Call%20other%20matters%E2%80%9D%20relating%20to%20citizenship%2C%20it%20still%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20give%20it%20%E2%80%98the%20absolute%20power%20to%20do%20so%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20observed%20in%C2%A0%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjudgments.ecourts.gov.in%2FKBJ%2F%3Fp%3Dhome%2Fintro%5C%22%3EKesavananda%20Bharati%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20there%20also%20exist%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eimplied%20limitations%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0that%20flow%20from%20the%20structure%20of%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20the%20%3Cem%3Eimplied%20limitation%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20present%20case%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%2C%20in%20Bhatia%E2%80%99s%20legal%20reasoning%20(one%20that%20can%20be%20generally%20agreed%20upon)%2C%20is%20the%20constitutional%20principle%20of%20%3Cem%3Esecularism%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3ESecularism%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjudgments.ecourts.gov.in%2FKBJ%2F%3Fp%3Dhome%2Fintro%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EKesavananda%20Bharati%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20held%2C%20is%20a%20basic%20feature%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20(independent%20of%20its%20subsequent%20insertion%20into%20the%20Preamble%20during%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Emergency).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Constitution%20commits%20us%20to%20being%20a%20secular%20polity.%20The%20key%20issue%2C%20then%2C%20is%20that%20can%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Econditions%20of%20entry%20into%20the%20polity%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E(determined%20by%20citizenship%20law)%20be%20such%20that%20they%20frustrate%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3Echaracter%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Eof%20the%20polity%20itself.%20The%20answer%2C%20obviously%2C%20is%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3Eno%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E.%20(emphasis%20in%20bold%20provided)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20other%20words%2C%20therefore%2C%20there%20is%20an%20%3Cem%3Eimplied%20limitation%3C%2Fem%3E%20upon%20the%20power%20under%20Article%2011%20to%20grant%20or%20withdraw%20citizenship%2C%20that%20does%20not%20permit%20Parliament%20to%20pass%20any%20such%20law%20that%20would%20negate%20the%20secular%20character%20of%20the%20polity%20%E2%80%93%20in%20this%20case%2C%20through%20the%20backdoor%2C%20by%20creating%20conditions%20of%20entry%20where%20religious%20claims%20become%20determinants%20of%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20put%20it%20in%20a%20single%20sentence%3A%20the%20principle%20of%20secularism%20acts%20as%20an%20implied%20limitation%20upon%20Parliament%E2%80%99s%20power%20to%20legislate%20on%20citizenship.%20Parliament%2C%20therefore%2C%20has%20all%20powers%20to%20prescribe%20conditions%20of%20citizenship%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eexcept%20and%20insofar%20as%20such%20conditions%20frustrate%20the%20Constitutional%20commitment%20towards%20preserving%20a%20secular%20polity.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FQ2O2NZWkN_A%3Fsi%3DVS5KhVKZmulwtx8S%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20indifference%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGoing%20beyond%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20act%20of%20judicial%20deference%20and%20deflection%20away%20from%20its%20own%20juridical%20responsibility%20in%20reviewing%20the%20CAA%2C%20in%20a%20hot%20election%20season%2C%20as%20the%20CAA%20gets%20notified%20weeks%20before%20the%20upcoming%20polls%2C%20one%20would%20have%20imagined%20a%20more%20vivid%20response%20from%20the%20political%20opposition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Pratap%20Bhanu%20Mehta%20rightly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fdiscrimination-not-justice-6173881%2F%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20in%20an%20insolent%20tyranny%2C%20whose%20hallmark%20is%20that%20it%20will%20take%20the%20calls%20for%20ordinary%20justice%2C%20decency%20and%20liberty%20as%20signs%20of%20%E2%80%98anti-national%20insurrection%E2%80%99.%20Its%20cause%20is%20served%20by%20portraying%20everything%20as%20disorder%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20INDIA%20bloc%2C%20as%20clueless%20and%20organisationally%20incohesive%20it%20seems%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20has%20done%20nothing%20to%20counter%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20a%20few%20chief%20ministers%20(like%20of%20Tamil%20Nadu%20or%20West%20Bengal)%2C%20most%20leaders%20of%20the%20opposition%20haven%E2%80%99t%20done%20much%20(beyond%20posting%20on%20social%20media%20handles)%20in%20challenging%20the%20unconstitutionality%20of%20the%20CAA%20and%20fighting%20the%20law%20tooth-and-nail%20by%20taking%20this%20to%20the%20streets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20political%20opposition%20(led%20by%20the%20Congress)%20may%20yet%20again%20outsource%20street%20protests%20against%20the%20CAA%E2%80%99s%20discriminatory%20intent%20to%20aggrieved%20groups%2C%20individuals%20and%20older%20women%20rather%20than%20present%20a%20more%20united%2C%20coordinated%20and%20cohesive%20strategy%20going%20into%20the%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20deafening%20noise%20of%20an%20observed%20%E2%80%98silence%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20in%20protecting%20minority%20rights%20%E2%80%93%20may%20also%20reflect%20the%20degree%20of%20the%20illiberal%20turn%20taken%20of%20late%20by%20most%20of%20the%20principal%20political%20opposition%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20signals%20their%20miserable%20failure%20in%20committing%20to%20the%20constitutionally%20safeguarded%20principle%20(and%20practice)%20of%20%3Cem%3Esecularism%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewhile%20taking%20on%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20divisive%20politics%20head-on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201970s%2C%20during%20the%20period%20of%20the%20Emergency%2C%20a%20unifying%20political%20oppositional%20architecture%20was%20evident%20because%20of%20the%20leadership%20of%20Jayaprakash%20Narayan%20(JP)%20and%20other%20leaders%20leading%20the%20fight%20against%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20oppressive%20regime%2C%20and%20their%20ability%20to%20include%20those%20affected%20by%20poor%20economic%20and%20social%20conditions%20(workers%2C%20farmers%20etc.).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Bharat%20Jodo%20Yatra%20(1.0%20or%202.0)%20has%20garnered%20little%20support%20in%20uniting%20the%20Indian%20political%20opposition%20against%20the%20BJP%2C%20and%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20seems%20to%20be%20headed%20nowhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%2C%20one%20of%20the%20critical%20differences%20between%20now%20and%20then%20(the%201970s)%20is%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20JP-style%2C%20exemplary%20form%20of%20opposition-uniting%2C%20cohesive%20public%20leadership%20(especially%20in%20the%20main%20political%20opposition)%20that%20can%20unite%20all%20political%20parties%20to%20challenge%20the%20Modi%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20hateful%20and%20divisive%20ideological%20agenda.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERahul%20Gandhi%20or%20the%20Congress%20have%20failed%20to%20exercise%20this%20kind%20of%20leadership%2C%20which%20is%20hurting%20the%20electoral%20possibilities%20of%20a%20national-level%20political%20coalition%20that%20can%20fight%20against%20the%20incumbent%20while%20offering%20a%20more%20promising%20counter-narrative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20courts%20too%20haven%E2%80%99t%20stood%20up%20to%20the%20authoritarian%20incumbent%20%E2%80%93%20i.e.%20to%20Modi%20%E2%80%93%20as%20they%20did%20to%20the%20Congress%20in%20the%201970s%20(during%20Indira%E2%80%99s%20regime).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%201970s%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20stood%20its%20ground%20in%20upholding%20the%20constitution%E2%80%99s%20basic%20structure%20and%20in%20attempting%20to%20protect%20basic%20civic%20and%20political%20rights.%20For%20now%2C%20the%20court%20appears%2C%20sadly%2C%20to%20be%20subjugated%20in%20agency%20and%20form%20as%20well%20as%20heavily%20%3Cem%3Eexecutivised%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20acting%20in%20the%20interest%20and%20representation%20of%20the%20government%20%E2%80%93%20to%20a%20great%20extent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20leadership%20and%20vital%20democratic%20institutions%20fail%20in%20upholding%20civic-institutional%20and%20constitutional%20morality%2C%20one%20can%20only%20hope%20that%20the%20practice%20of%20popular%20social%20movements%20against%20a%20regime%20can%20find%20a%20new%20voice%20and%20form%20this%20election%20through%20the%20kind%20of%20movement%20that%20was%20led%20earlier%20in%20the%20street%20protests%20(back%20in%202019)%20against%20the%20CAA-NRC%20combine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20a%20movement%20must%20be%20led%20by%20the%20educated%2C%20young%20and%20old%3B%20united%20across%20India%3B%20and%20one%20whose%20sustenance%20can%20perhaps%20establish%20a%20new%20normal%20in%20restoring%20%3Cem%3Ehope%3C%2Fem%3E%20among%20the%20future%20generations%20in%20a%20united%20India%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20acknowledge%20(and%20live%20with)%20its%20own%20differences%20and%20counter%20the%20violent%20politics%20of%20a%20brutish%20majoritarianism%20that%20a%20regime%20may%20seek%20to%20entrench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fdeepanshu-mohan%2F%5C%22%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20Professor%20of%20Economics%2C%20Dean%2C%20IDEAS%2C%20Office%20of%20InterDisciplinary%20Studies%2C%20and%20Director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%20(CNES)%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%20He%20is%20a%20Visiting%20Professor%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20a%202024%20Fall%20Academic%20Visitor%20to%20Faculty%20of%20Asian%20and%20Middle%20Eastern%20Studies%2C%20University%20of%20Oxford.%20He%20has%20held%20Visiting%20Professorships%20with%20University%20of%20London%E2%80%99s%20Birkbeck%20College%20(UK)%2C%20University%20of%20Ottawa%20(Canada)%2C%20Carleton%20University%20(Canada)%2C%20Stellenbosch%20University%20(South%20Africa)%2C%20FGV%20(Rio%2C%20Brazil)%20in%20the%20past.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710563425000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fu