20media%2C%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20is%20seen%20exiting%20the%20stadium%20when%20someone%20from%20the%20crowd%20asks%20him%20about%20his%20health.%20The%20actor%20is%20initially%20seen%20gesturing%20with%20his%20hands%20that%20everything%20is%20fine.%20The%20person%20then%20asked%20him%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20are%20you%3F%20All%20fine%3F%20to%20which%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BFake%20news.%26quot%3B%20The%20reports%20started%20in%20the%20afternoon%20with%20some%20saying%20he%20had%20gone%20to%20the%20Kokilaben%20Dhirubhai%20Ambani%20Hospital%20for%20a%20routine%20check.%20Others%20said%20he%20was%20hospitalised%20for%20an%20angioplasty%20--%20a%20balloon%20procedure%20to%20open%20up%20blocked%20arteries%20and%20blood%20vessels%20--%20to%20remove%20a%20blockage%20in%20his%20leg.%20And%20there%20were%20some%20who%20reported%20he%20had%20an%20angioplasty%20for%20a%20blocked%20artery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20was%20no%20confirmation%20from%20either%20the%20hospital%20or%20his%20office%20for%20much%20of%20the%20day.%20And%20though%20the%20reports%20could%20not%20be%20independently%20verified%2C%20%23Amitabh%20Bachchan%20and%20%23Kokilaben%20Hospital%20were%20top%20trends%20on%20X.%20Among%20those%20who%20wrote%20were%20Congress%20leader%20Sanjay%20Nirupam.%20%E2%80%9CPraying%20for%20Amitabh%20Bachchan's%20speedy%20recovery.%20%23AmitabhBachchan%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20posted%20on%20X.%20Scores%20of%20others%20wrote%20wishing%20him%20to%20get%20well%20soon%20and%20that%20they%20were%20praying%20for%20his%20good%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmitabh%20Bachchan%20was%20last%20seen%20in%20a%20cameo%20appearance%20in%20Tiger%20Shroff's%20%3Ci%3EGanapath%3C%2Fi%3E.%20His%20upcoming%20films%20include%20Deepika%20Padukone%20and%20Prabhas-starrer%20%3Ci%3EKalki%20AD%202898%3C%2Fi%3E.%20He%20will%20also%20be%20seen%20alongside%20Rajinikanth%20in%20the%20Tamil%20film%20%3Ci%3EVettaiyan%3C%2Fi%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710561840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fv3lbl4oo_big_625x300_16_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Famitabh-bachchan-watches-ispla-match-after-angioplasty-reports-says-fake-news-5248285%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Amitabh%20Bachchan's%20recent%20appearance%20was%20in%20a%20cameo%20role%20in%20Tiger%20Shroff's%20Ganapath%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Famitabh-bachchan-watches-ispla-match-after-angioplasty-reports-says-fake-news-5248285%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Famitabh-bachchan-watches-ispla-match-after-angioplasty-reports-says-fake-news-5248285%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Famitabh-bachchan-watches-ispla-match-after-angioplasty-reports-says-fake-news-5248285%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI%20Starts%20Creating%20Fake%20Legal%20Cases%2C%20Making%20Its%20Way%20Into%20Real%20Courtrooms%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EWe've%20seen%20deepfake%2C%20explicit%20images%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F01%2F26%2Farts%2Fmusic%2Ftaylor-swift-ai-fake-images.html%5C%22%3Ecelebrities%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20created%20by%20artificial%20intelligence%20(AI).%20AI%20has%20also%20played%20a%20hand%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-ghosts-of-the-past-pop-music-is-haunted-by-our-anxieties-about-the-future-218555%5C%22%3Ecreating%20music%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fbringing-ai-up-to-speed-autonomous-auto-racing-promises-safer-driverless-cars-on-the-road-214208%5C%22%3Edriverless%20race%20cars%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20spreading%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fmisinformation-how-fact-checking-journalism-is-evolving-and-having-a-real-impact-on-the-world-218379%5C%22%3Emisinformation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20among%20other%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20hardly%20surprising%2C%20then%2C%20that%20AI%20also%20has%20a%20strong%20impact%20on%20our%20legal%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20well%20known%20that%20courts%20must%20decide%20disputes%20based%20on%20the%20law%2C%20which%20is%20presented%20by%20lawyers%20to%20the%20court%20as%20part%20of%20a%20client's%20case.%20It's%20therefore%20highly%20concerning%20that%20fake%20law%2C%20invented%20by%20AI%2C%20is%20being%20used%20in%20legal%20disputes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20does%20this%20pose%20issues%20of%20legality%20and%20ethics%2C%20it%20also%20threatens%20to%20undermine%20faith%20and%20trust%20in%20global%20legal%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20do%20fake%20laws%20come%20about%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20little%20doubt%20that%20generative%20AI%20is%20a%20powerful%20tool%20with%20transformative%20potential%20for%20society%2C%20including%20many%20aspects%20of%20the%20legal%20system.%20But%20its%20use%20comes%20with%20responsibilities%20and%20risks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELawyers%20are%20trained%20to%20carefully%20apply%20professional%20knowledge%20and%20experience%2C%20and%20are%20generally%20not%20big%20risk-takers.%20However%2C%20some%20unwary%20lawyers%20(and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freason.com%2Fvolokh%2F2023%2F11%2F13%2Fself-represented-litigants-use-ai-to-write-briefs-produce-hallucinated-citations%2F%5C%22%3Eself-represented%3C%2Fa%3E%20litigants)%20have%20been%20caught%20out%20by%20artificial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAI%20models%20are%20trained%20on%20massive%20data%20sets.%20When%20prompted%20by%20a%20user%2C%20they%20can%20create%20new%20content%20(both%20text%20and%20audiovisual).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20content%20generated%20this%20way%20can%20look%20very%20convincing%2C%20it%20can%20also%20be%20inaccurate.%20This%20is%20the%20result%20of%20the%20AI%20model%20attempting%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfill%20in%20the%20gaps%E2%80%9D%20when%20its%20training%20data%20is%20inadequate%20or%20flawed%2C%20and%20is%20commonly%20referred%20to%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csiro.au%2Fen%2Fnews%2FAll%2FArticles%2F2023%2FJune%2Fhumans-and-ai-hallucinate%5C%22%3Ehallucination%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20contexts%2C%20generative%20AI%20hallucination%20is%20not%20a%20problem.%20Indeed%2C%20it%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20an%20example%20of%20creativity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20AI%20hallucinated%20or%20created%20inaccurate%20content%20that%20is%20then%20used%20in%20legal%20processes%2C%20that's%20a%20problem%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20when%20combined%20with%20time%20pressures%20on%20lawyers%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20access%20to%20legal%20services%20for%20many.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20potent%20combination%20can%20result%20in%20carelessness%20and%20shortcuts%20in%20legal%20research%20and%20document%20preparation%2C%20potentially%20creating%20reputational%20issues%20for%20the%20legal%20profession%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20public%20trust%20in%20the%20administration%20of%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EIt's%20happening%20already%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20best%20known%20generative%20AI%20%E2%80%9Cfake%20case%E2%80%9D%20is%20the%202023%20US%20case%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flaw.justia.com%2Fcases%2Ffederal%2Fdistrict-courts%2Fnew-york%2Fnysdce%2F1%3A2022cv01461%2F575368%2F54%2F%5C%22%3EMata%20v%20Avianca%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20which%20lawyers%20submitted%20a%20brief%20containing%20fake%20extracts%20and%20case%20citations%20to%20a%20New%20York%20court.%20The%20brief%20was%20researched%20using%20ChatGPT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyers%2C%20unaware%20that%20ChatGPT%20can%20hallucinate%2C%20failed%20to%20check%20that%20the%20cases%20actually%20existed.%20The%20consequences%20were%20disastrous.%20Once%20the%20error%20was%20uncovered%2C%20the%20court%20dismissed%20their%20client's%20case%2C%20sanctioned%20the%20lawyers%20for%20acting%20in%20bad%20faith%2C%20fined%20them%20and%20their%20firm%2C%20and%20exposed%20their%20actions%20to%20public%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20adverse%20publicity%2C%20other%20fake%20case%20examples%20continue%20to%20surface.%20Michael%20Cohen%2C%20Donald%20Trump's%20former%20lawyer%2C%20gave%20his%20own%20lawyer%20cases%20generated%20by%20Google%20Bard%2C%20another%20generative%20AI%20chatbot.%20He%20believed%20they%20were%20real%20(they%20were%20not)%20and%20that%20his%20lawyer%20would%20fact%20check%20them%20(he%20did%20not).%20His%20lawyer%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Flegal%2Fex-trump-fixer-michael-cohen-says-ai-created-fake-cases-court-filing-2023-12-29%5C%22%3Eincluded%20the%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20brief%20filed%20with%20the%20US%20Federal%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFake%20cases%20have%20also%20surfaced%20in%20recent%20matters%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbc.ca%2Fnews%2Fcanada%2Fbritish-columbia%2Flawyer-chatgpt-fake-precedent-1.7126393%5C%22%3ECanada%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.legalfutures.co.uk%2Flatest-news%2Flitigant-unwittingly-put-fake-cases-generated-by-ai-before-tribunal%5C%22%3Ethe%20United%20Kingdom%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20trend%20goes%20unchecked%2C%20how%20can%20we%20ensure%20that%20the%20careless%20use%20of%20generative%20AI%20does%20not%20undermine%20the%20public's%20trust%20in%20the%20legal%20system%3F%20Consistent%20failures%20by%20lawyers%20to%20exercise%20due%20care%20when%20using%20these%20tools%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20mislead%20and%20congest%20the%20courts%2C%20harm%20clients'%20interests%2C%20and%20generally%20undermine%20the%20rule%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat's%20being%20done%20about%20it%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20world%2C%20legal%20regulators%20and%20courts%20have%20responded%20in%20various%20ways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20US%20state%20bars%20and%20courts%20have%20issued%20guidance%2C%20opinions%20or%20orders%20on%20generative%20AI%20use%2C%20ranging%20from%20responsible%20adoption%20to%20an%20outright%20ban.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELaw%20societies%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20British%20Columbia%2C%20and%20the%20courts%20of%20New%20Zealand%2C%20have%20also%20developed%20guidelines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Australia%2C%20the%20NSW%20Bar%20Association%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Finbrief.nswbar.asn.au%2Fposts%2F9e292ee2fc90581f795ff1df0105692d%2Fattachment%2FNSW%2520Bar%2520Association%2520GPT%2520AI%2520Language%2520Models%2520Guidelines.pdf%5C%22%3Egenerative%20AI%20guide%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20barristers.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flsj.com.au%2Farticles%2Fa-solicitors-guide-to-responsible-use-of-artificial-intelligence%2F%5C%22%3ELaw%20Society%20of%20NSW%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.liv.asn.au%2FWeb%2FLaw_Institute_Journal_and_News%2FWeb%2FLIJ%2FYear%2F2023%2F09September%2FHow_lawyers_are_using_generative_AI.aspx%5C%22%3ELaw%20Institute%20of%20Victoria%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20released%20articles%20on%20responsible%20use%20in%20line%20with%20solicitors'%20conduct%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20lawyers%20and%20judges%2C%20like%20the%20public%2C%20will%20have%20some%20understanding%20of%20generative%20AI%20and%20can%20recognise%20both%20its%20limits%20and%20benefits.%20But%20there%20are%20others%20who%20may%20not%20be%20as%20aware.%20Guidance%20undoubtedly%20helps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20mandatory%20approach%20is%20needed.%20Lawyers%20who%20use%20generative%20AI%20tools%20cannot%20treat%20it%20as%20a%20substitute%20for%20exercising%20their%20own%20judgement%20and%20diligence%2C%20and%20must%20check%20the%20accuracy%20and%20reliability%20of%20the%20information%20they%20receive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Australia%2C%20courts%20should%20adopt%20practice%20notes%20or%20rules%20that%20set%20out%20expectations%20when%20generative%20AI%20is%20used%20in%20litigation.%20Court%20rules%20can%20also%20guide%20self-represented%20litigants%2C%20and%20would%20communicate%20to%20the%20public%20that%20our%20courts%20are%20aware%20of%20the%20problem%20and%20are%20addressing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20profession%20could%20also%20adopt%20formal%20guidance%20to%20promote%20the%20responsible%20use%20of%20AI%20by%20lawyers.%20At%20the%20very%20least%2C%20technology%20competence%20should%20become%20a%20requirement%20of%20lawyers'%20continuing%20legal%20education%20in%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetting%20clear%20requirements%20for%20the%20responsible%20and%20ethical%20use%20of%20generative%20AI%20by%20lawyers%20in%20Australia%20will%20encourage%20appropriate%20adoption%20and%20shore%20up%20public%20confidence%20in%20our%20lawyers%2C%20our%20courts%2C%20and%20the%20overall%20administration%20of%20justice%20in%20this%20country.%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F225080%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3Cstrong%3EAuthors%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fmichael-legg-5988%5C%22%3EMichael%20Legg%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20Law%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funsw-sydney-1414%5C%22%3EUNSW%20Sydney%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fvicki-mcnamara-1516854%5C%22%3EVicki%20McNamara%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Senior%20Research%20Associate%2C%20Centre%20for%20the%20Future%20of%20the%20Legal%20Profession%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funsw-sydney-1414%5C%22%3EUNSW%20Sydney%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3C