sture%20and%20natural%20oils.%20Other%20hair%20types%2C%20like%20thick%2C%20coarse%2C%20or%20oily%2C%20will%20likely%20do%20just%20fine%20with%20the%20powerful%20cleanse%20from%20products%20with%20sulfates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWho%20will%20benefit%20from%20a%20sulfate-free%20shampoo%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20individuals%20can%20benefit%20from%20using%20a%20sulfate-free%20shampoo.%20A%20sulfate-free%20product%20is%20a%20safe%20choice%20if%20you%20have%20sensitive%20skin%20or%20dry%2C%20damaged%2C%20color-treated%2C%20or%20textured%20hair.%20Since%20products%20without%20sulfates%20are%20known%20to%20be%20more%20gentle%2C%20you'll%20experience%20less%20scalp%20irritation%2C%20hair%20dryness%2C%20and%20color%20fading.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EDo%20sulfate-free%20shampoos%20clean%20your%20hair%20as%20well%20as%20sulfate%20shampoos%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAgain%2C%20it%20depends%20on%20your%20hair%20type%20and%20needs.%20For%20some%20hair%20types%2C%20sulfate%20shampoos%20might%20clean%20hair%20a%20little%20too%20well%2C%20leaving%20it%20feeling%20more%20like%20straw%20than%20silk.%20Even%20if%20your%20hair%20is%20thick%2C%20coarse%2C%20and%2For%20oily%2C%20you%20can%20still%20get%20a%20great%20clean%20without%20sulfates%3B%20just%20don't%20expect%20the%20same%20thick%2C%20foamy%20lather%20you%20get%20with%20a%20sulfate%20shampoo.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20don't%20wash%20their%20hair%20often%2C%20a%20sulfate%20option%20might%20actually%20be%20a%20good%20choice.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20shampoo%20your%20hair%20infrequently%2C%20it%20can%20be%20more%20challenging%20to%20sufficiently%20cleanse%20your%20scalp%20due%20to%20increased%20product%20and%20sebum%20build-up%2C%26quot%3B%20Reslan%20explained.%20%26quot%3BFor%20those%20who%20shampoo%20daily%2C%20sulfate-free%20shampoos%20will%20do%20the%20trick.%26quot%3B%20If%20you%20don't%20shampoo%20frequently%2C%20Reslan%20recommends%20alternating%20weekly%20with%20a%20sulfate%20shampoo%20to%20remove%20all%20the%20build