0group%20the%20third-highest%20political%20funder%2C%20after%20the%20Tamil%20Nadu-based%20lottery%20firm%20Future%20Gaming%20and%20Hotel%20Services%20PR%20(Rs%201%2C368%20crore)%20and%20Megha%20Engineering%20%26amp%3B%20Infrastructures%20Ltd%20(Rs%20966%20crore).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOf%20Jalan%E2%80%99s%20group%20of%20companies%2C%20Keventer%20Foodpark%20Infra%20Limited%20purchased%20204%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20195%20crore%2C%20Madanlal%20Ltd.%20purchased%20199%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20185.5%20crore%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mkjenterprises.in%2Fbod.php%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.mkjenterprises.in%2Fbod.php%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710595078224000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0hM-WF_a8urD8GsbO74FHT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMKJ%20Enterprises%20Ltd%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0purchased%20324%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20192.42%20crore%20and%20Sasmal%20Infrastructure%20Private%20Limited%20purchased%2044%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2044%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20payments%20made%20through%20Keventer%20Foodpark%20and%20Madanlal%20came%20at%20a%20crucial%20time%20%E2%80%93%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20in%20West%20Bengal%20%E2%80%93%20Rs%2055%20crore%20on%20April%2016%2C%20Rs%2075%20crore%20on%20May%207%2C%20and%20Rs%2065%20crore%20on%20May%208%20through%20Keventer%20and%20Rs.%20110%20crore%20on%20May%208%20and%20Rs%2075.5%20crore%20on%20May%2010%20through%20Madanlal%20Ltd.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%202021%20Assembly%20election%20in%20West%20Bengal%20was%20held%20in%20seven%20phases%20from%20April%2011%20to%20May%2019.%20This%20means%20that%20they%20purchased%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20380%20crore%20during%20the%20election%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhile%20it%20is%20not%20yet%20clear%20from%20the%20available%20data%20set%20(as%20the%20serial%20numbers%20of%20the%20bonds%20have%20not%20yet%20been%20published)%20to%20determine%20who%20received%20how%20much%20of%20this%20funding%2C%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20party%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20the%20main%20beneficiary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20records%20uploaded%20by%20the%20ECI%20on%20Thursday%2C%20the%20TMC%20encashed%20Rs%2017%20crore%20on%20April%2016%2C%20Rs%2075%20lakh%20on%20April%2022%2C%20Rs%205%20crore%20on%20May%208%2C%20Rs%2027.8%20crore%20on%20May%2014%2C%20and%20Rs%201%20crore%20on%20May%2022.%20This%20means%2C%20the%20TMC%20cumulatively%20got%20Rs%2051.6%20crore%20from%20all%20fundings%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20during%20the%202019%20election%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EUnderstandably%2C%20Jalan%20funded%20some%20other%20parties%20the%20most%2C%20even%20though%20his%20business%20interests%20are%20mostly%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20even%20though%20they%20have%20footprints%20outside%20the%20state%20and%20plan%20to%20expand%20their%20agro%2C%20dairy%20and%20food%20processing%20business%20to%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20saw%20the%20BJP%20carrying%20out%20a%20high-voltage%20campaign%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20with%20star%20campaigners%20including%20heavyweight%20Union%20ministers%20and%20various%20BJP-ruled%20state%E2%80%99s%20chief%20ministers%20making%20repeated%20visits%20to%20address%20multiple%20rallies.%20The%20saffron%20party%20recorded%20an%20unprecedented%20surge%20%E2%80%93%20increasing%20its%20Lok%20Sabha%20tally%20from%20the%20state%20from%202%20in%202014%20to%2018%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIt%20is%20interesting%20to%20note%20that%20after%20Bengal%20Congress%20president%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20alleged%20a%20scam%20in%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20sale%20of%20Metro%20Diary%20shares%20to%20Keventer%20Agro%2C%20one%20of%20the%20group%20companies%2C%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20started%20a%20probe%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FBJP4Bengal%2Fphotos%2Fa.150306445049641%2F1539678112779127%2F%3Ftype%3D3%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FBJP4Bengal%2Fphotos%2Fa.150306445049641%2F1539678112779127%2F%3Ftype%253D3%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1710595078224000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw0kk4XTY-9U3j6u_zyPVJiP%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20October%202017%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20spoke%20to%20the%20Keventer%20group%20management%20a%20few%20times%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%20post-Lok%20Sabha%20election%20scenario%2C%20the%20probe%20focused%20more%20on%20TMC%20MLAs%20and%20government%20officials.%20The%20Jalan%20group%20of%20companies%E2%80%99%20funding%20through%20electoral%20bonds%20was%20also%20reduced%20in%20the%20post-2019%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20payments%20from%20MKJ%20Enterprises%20came%20between%20October%204%2C%202019%2C%20and%20November%2018%2C%202023.%20Those%20from%20Sasmal%20Infrastructure%20came%20between%20November%208%202023%20and%20January%2011%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EGoing%20by%20the%20health%20of%20the%20companies%20that%20purchased%20the%20bonds%2C%20Sasmal%20Infrastructure%20has%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zaubacorp.com%2Fcompany%2FSASMAL-INFRASTRUCTURE-PRIVATE-LIMITED%2FU74999WB2012PTC174637%23google_vignette%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.zaubacorp.com%2Fcompany%2FSASMAL-INFRASTRUCTURE-PRIVATE-LIMITED%2FU74999WB2012PTC174637%2523google_vignette%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust