ess-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fpaytm-payments-bank-releases-faqs-on-refund-closing-fastag-accounts-124031500957_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fpaytm-payments-bank-releases-faqs-on-refund-closing-fastag-accounts-124031500957_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fpaytm-payments-bank-releases-faqs-on-refund-closing-fastag-accounts-124031500957_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20Takers%20For%20BRS%20Tickets%3F%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao%20Faces%20Challenges%20Ahead%20Of%20Lok%20Sabha%20Polls%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15145016%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-15-at-2.35.07-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHyderabad%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20facing%20defeat%20in%20assembly%20elections%20three%20months%20ago%2C%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samiti%20(BRS)%20which%20was%20high%20on%20expansion%20mode%20beyond%20the%20frontiers%20of%20Telangana%20earlier%20is%20now%20fishing%20in%20troubled%20waters%20even%20to%20find%20candidates%20to%20contest%20the%20upcoming%20parliamentary%20elections.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EOn%20Wednesday%20evening%20(March%2013)%20when%20BRS%20president%20and%20former%20chief%20minister%20K.%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao%20chaired%20a%20meeting%20of%20party%20leaders%20to%20select%20some%20candidates%20it%20was%20obvious%20that%20his%20hands%20were%20tied%20in%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOut%20of%20nine%20sitting%20MPs%20of%20the%20BRS%2C%20three%20have%20quit%20the%20party%20while%20two%20have%20expressed%20unwillingness%20to%20contest%20and%20one%20was%20elected%20as%20an%20MLA.%20The%20remaining%20three%20were%20renominated.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EChandrashekhar%20Rao%20dropped%20his%20daughter%20and%20MLC%20K.%20Kavitha%2C%20who%20was%20a%20strong%20contender%20for%20the%20ticket%20from%20Nizamabad%20seat%20which%20she%20had%20represented%20from%202014%20to%202019.%20Notably%2C%20Kavitha%20had%20vowed%20to%20avenge%20her%20defeat%20in%20the%20last%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20BJP%20candidate%20Dharmapuri%20Arvind%20but%20was%20replaced%20by%20former%20BRS%20MLA%20Bajireddy%20Goverdhan.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EKavitha%E2%80%99s%20omission%20was%20traced%20to%20her%20alleged%20links%20in%20the%20Delhi%20liquor%20scam.%20She%20is%20alleged%20to%20be%20a%20member%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98South%20Group%E2%80%99%20that%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20making%20payoffs%20of%20Rs%20100%20crore%20in%20cartelisation%20of%20liquor%20trade%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Friday%20(March%2015)%2C%20Kavitha%20was%20arrested%20after%20the%20Income%20Tax%20and%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20carried%20out%20raids%20at%20her%20residence%20and%20related%20premises%20amidst%20protests%20by%20the%20BRS%20cadre.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EEarlier%2C%20she%20was%20questioned%20by%20the%20ED%20three%20times%20on%20charges%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20included%20as%20an%20accused%20by%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20in%20the%20case.%20Her%20petition%20seeking%20protection%20from%20arrest%20and%20challenging%20summons%20issued%20by%20the%20ED%20is%20scheduled%20for%20hearing%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20March%2019.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20BRS%20chief%20also%20replaced%20sitting%20MP%20of%20Chevella%20G.%20Ranjeet%20Reddy%20with%20Kasani%20Gnaneshwar%20who%20had%20resigned%20as%20the%20state%20president%20of%20Telugu%20Desam%20Party%20(TDP)%20ahead%20of%20the%20assembly%20elections%20after%20the%20party%20decided%20not%20to%20contest%20polls%20in%20Telangana.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EAnother%20sitting%20MP%20Pasunuri%20Dayakar%20of%20Warangal%20(SC%20reserved)%20constituency%20was%20replaced%20with%20former%20minister%20Kadiyam%20Srihari%E2%80%99s%20daughter%20Dr%20Kadiyam%20Kavya.%20%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Dayakar%20called%20on%20chief%20minister%20A.%20Revanth%20Reddy%20at%20the%20Secretariat.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EIn%20Zaheerabad%20seat%2C%20lesser%20known%20leader%20Gali%20Anil%20Kumar%20was%20chosen%20to%20fill%20the%20void%20created%20by%20the%20resignation%20of%20sitting%20MP%20B.B.%20Patil.%20Patil%20quit%20BRS%20to%20join%20the%20BJP%20which%20offered%20him%20the%20ticket%20from%20the%20same%20constituency%20within%20hours.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EAlthough%20it%20was%20known%20that%20Kavitha%20might%20not%20be%20fielded%20by%20the%20party%20this%20time%2C%20the%20development%20in%20Chevella%20raised%20quite%20a%20few%20eye%20brows%20as%20Ranjeet%20Reddy%20refused%20to%20contest%20the%20polls%20and%20withdrew%20at%20a%20time%20when%20he%20had%20earned%20quite%20a%20good%20reputation%20in%20the%20party.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDrama%20in%20the%20BRS%20meeting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20candidate%20selection%20meeting%20in%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20residence%20on%20Wednesday%20was%20also%20attended%20by%20former%20BRS%20MLA%20Aroori%20Ramesh%20who%20was%20involved%20in%20a%20road%20rage%20incident%20earlier%20in%20the%20day.%20Ramesh%E2%80%99s%20shirt%20was%20torn%20by%20his%20followers%20while%20he%20was%20heading%20to%20Hyderabad%20in%20a%20car.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3ERamesh%20had%20shown%20his%20inclination%20to%20join%20the%20BJP%20earlier%20and%20had%20also%20spoken%20to%20the%20BRS%20state%20president%20G.%20Kishan%20Reddy%20in%20this%20regard.%20However%2C%20senior%20BRS%20leaders%20such%20as%20former%20minister%20T.%20Harish%20Rao%20tried%20to%20counsel%20him%20against%20quitting%20the%20party%20but%20he%20was%20allegedly%20not%20convinced.%20Finally%2C%20former%20minister%20E.%20Dayakar%20Rao%20landed%20at%20his%20house%20in%20Warangal%20and%20whisked%20him%20away%20in%20his%20car%20to%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EAngry%20BJP%20supporters%20intercepted%20the%20car%20at%20Pembarthi%20on%20Warangal-Hyderabad%20highway%20and%20heckled%20Ramesh.%20They%20shouted%20at%20him%20for%20ditching%20the%20BJP%20after%20promising%20to%20join%20the%20saffron%20party.%20The%20angry%20crowd%20allowed%20him%20to%20leave%20only%20when%20Ramesh%20gave%20the%20assurance%20that%20he%20would%20convey%20to%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao%20his%20unwillingness%20to%20contest%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20BRS.%20He%20promptly%20kept%20his%20word%20at%20the%20meeting%20with%20the%20BRS%20chief%20even%20as%20the%20latter%20advised%20him%20not%20to%20take%20any%20hasty%20step.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EBRS%E2%80%99s%20T.%20Harish%20Rao%20remarked%20that%20poaching%20of%20party%20candidates%20by%20the%20BJP%20or%20Congress%20showed%20that%20they%20did%20not%20have%20able%20leaders%20to%20field%20for%20the%20upcoming%20elections.%20He%20recalled%20a%20call%20given%20by%20chief%20minister%20Revanth%20Reddy%20as%20Opposition%20leader%2C%20asking%20people%20to%20attack%20defectors%20with%20stones.%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20is%20he%20promoting%20defections%20now%3F%2C%E2%80%9D%20T.%20Harish%20Rao%20questioned.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBRS-BSP%20coalition%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20internal%20BRS%20meeting%20was%20followed%20by%20another%20round%20of%20consultations%20between%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao%20and%20a%20delegation%20of%20the%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20led%20by%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%20Ramji%20Gautam%20and%20BSP%20state%20president%20R.S.%20Praveen%20Kumar.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20two%20parties%20had%20entered%20into%20an%20alliance%20for%20the%20parliamentary%20elections.%20Gautam%20was%20sent%20as%20an%20emissary%20by%20BSP%20chief%20Mayawati%2C%20marking%20an%20exception%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Telangana%20as%20the%20party%20has%20decided%20to%20contest%20the%20elections%20alone%20at%20the%20national%20level.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EAfter%20the%20defeat%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao%20has%20also%20changed%20his%20stance%20on%20collaborating%20with%20other%20parties.%20He%20had%20earlier%20shrugged%20off%20requests%20from%20the%20Left%20parties%20for%20a%20tie%20up%20for%20the%20recently%20concluded%20assembly%20polls.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EIn%20the%20initial%20meeting%20a%20few%20days%20ago%2C%20Kumar%20indicated%20his%20interest%20to%20contest%20from%20Nagarkurnool%20(SC)%20constituency%20where%20a%20sitting%20MP%20of%20the%20BRS%20had%20quit%20the%20party%20to%20join%20the%20BJP.%20The%20BSP%20is%20also%20staking%20claim%20for%20the%20Adilabad%20(ST)%20seat.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBRS%E2%80%99s%20troubles%20not%20over%20yet%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20BRS%20had%20hassle%20free%20selection%20of%20candidates%20in%20four%20out%20of%20the%20nine%20constituencies%20that%20are%20finalised%20so%20far.%20In%20total%2C%20there%20are%2017%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituencies%20in%20the%20state%2C%20including%20three%20reserved%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SC)%20and%20two%20for%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(ST).%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EBarring%20Khammam%2C%20Mahbubnagar%2C%20Karimnagar%20and%20Mahbubabad%20(ST%20reserved)%20constituencies%2C%20the%20party%20had%20to%20literally%20scout%20for%20candidates%20in%20the%20other%20seats.%20The%20selection%20was%20not%20easy%20in%20respect%20of%20Nizamabad%2C%20Chevella%2C%20Warangal%20(SC)%2C%20Zaheerabad%20and%20Peddapalli%20(SC)%20constituencies.%20The%20party%20is%20yet%20to%20resolve%20candidatures%20for%20ticklish%20constituencies%20like%20Nalgonda%2C%20Bhongir%20and%20Malkajgiri.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20sitting%20MP%20of%20BRS%20from%20Peddapalli%20seat%2C%20Venkatesh%20Neta%2C%20has%20joined%20the%20Congress.%20In%20this%20constituency%2C%20the%20BRS%20gave%20the%20ticket%20to%20former%20minister%20Koppula%20Easwar%20who%20has%20lost%20the%20recent%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EAnother%20sitting%20MP%20of%20BRS%20from%20Medak%20seat%2C%20Kotha%20Prabhakar%20Reddy%2C%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20assembly%20which%20has%20driven%20the%20party%20to%20look%20for%20a%20new%20candidate.%20Vanteru%20Pratap%20Reddy%2C%20who%20had%20unsuccessfully%20contested%20election%20to%20the%20assembly%20last%20year%2C%20is%20tipped%20to%20be%20the%20candidate%20from%20Medak%20constituency.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20BRS%20also%20had%20a%20tough%20time%20in%20selecting%20candidates%20for%20Secunderabad%20and%20Malkajgiri%2C%20the%20latter%20particularly%20which%20is%20a%20high%20profile%20seat%20represented%20in%20the%20present%20term%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20by%20chief%20minister%20Revanth%20Reddy.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3ERevanth%20Reddy%20on%20Thursday%20(March%2014)%20visited%20the%20house%20of%20former%20MP%20of%20Mahbubnagar%20A.P.%20Jitender%20Reddy%20to%20persuade%20him%20to%20join%20the%20Congress%20and%20contest%20from%20Malkajgiri.%20Jitender%20Reddy%20was%20eyeing%20for%20the%20BJP%20ticket%20from%20Mahbubnagar%20but%20lost%20the%20race%20against%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20national%20vice-president%20D.K.%20Aruna.%20%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20a%20strong%20rumour%20on%20Friday%20that%20he%20might%20also%20go%20to%20the%20house%20of%20Ranjeet%20Reddy.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%C2%A0Sai%20Kiran%20who%20was%20the%20BRS%20candidate%20from%20the%20Secunderabad%20constituency%20in%202019%20also%20reportedly%20expressed%20his%20unwillingness%20to%20contest%20this%20time.%20He%20is%20the%20son%20of%20former%20minister%20T.%20Srinivas%20Yadav.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EReacting%20to%20the%20developments%2C%20former%20BRS%20MP%20and%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20from%20Karimnagar%2C%20B.%20Vinod%20Kumar%20said%20the%20party%20did%20not%20get%20%E2%80%9Cpotential%E2%80%9D%20candidates%20capable%20of%20winning%20though%20there%20were%20plenty%20of%20them%20willing%20to%20enter%20fray.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3ELeaders%20like%20Aroori%20Ramesh%20who%20were%20capable%20of%20winning%20were%20in%20%E2%80%9Cdouble%20mind%2C%E2%80%9D%20Vinod%20Kumar%20said.%C2%A0He%20underlined%20that%20the%20prospects%20of%20the%20party%20could%20be%20measured%20only%20after%20a%20fortnight.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20dir%3D%5C%22auto%5C%22%3EThe%20BRS%20was%20planning%20to%20expand%20to%20other%20states%20%E2%80%94%20even%20changed%20the%20part%20name%20from%20TRS%20(Telangana%20Samiti%20Rashtra)%20%E2%80%94%20until%20it%E2%80%99s%20defeat%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections.%20The%20party%20organised%20half%20a%20dozen%20rallies%20in%20Maharashtra%20and%20mobilised%20thousands%20of%20members%20in%20the%20western%20state.%20But%2C%20the%20leadership%20has%20now%20gone%20mute%20regarding%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20future%20there.%20Maharastra%20local%20leaders%20even%20alleged%20that%20their%20calls%20to%20senior%20party%20leaders%20remained%20unanswered%20and%20they%20were%20unsure%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20intentions%20now.%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710513050000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15145016%2FScreen-Shot-2024-03-15-at-2.35.07-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fno-takers-for-brs-tickets-chandrashekhar-rao-faces-challenges-ahead-of-lok-sabha-polls%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Many%20BRS%20leaders%20have%20joined%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20BJP%20recently.%20Meanwhile%2C%20BRS%20MLC%20K.%20Kavitha%20who%20is%20Chandrashekhar%20Rao's%20daughter%20and%20a%20former%20MP%20was%20arrested%20after%20the%20Income%20Tax%20and%20ED%20carried%20out%20raids%20at%20her%20residence%20and%20related%20premises%20am