ustice%20Done%20to%20the%20Language%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15180250%2FUntitled-design-43.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20days%20ago%2C%20the%20newly%20elected%20first%20woman%20chief%20minister%20of%20Pakistani%20Punjab%2C%20Maryam%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%20declared%20that%20her%20government%20will%20mandate%20the%20teaching%20of%20the%20Punjabi%20language%20in%20all%20the%20schools%20of%20the%20province.%20This%20made%20headlines%20in%20Pakistan%20and%20a%20number%20of%20commentators%20lauded%20this%20decision%20as%20historic.%20This%20must%20have%20confused%20the%20Punjabis%20on%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20Radcliffe%20Line%2C%20making%20them%20wonder%20why%20their%20fellow%20Punjabis%20in%20Pakistan%20did%20not%20teach%20their%20own%20language.%20After%20all%2C%20Pakistan%20has%20been%20independent%20for%20over%20seventy-five%20years%2C%20Punjab%20dominates%20the%20country%2C%20its%20military%20and%20bureaucracy%2C%20and%20yet%2C%20why%20is%20its%20language%20so%20neglected%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20answer%20lies%20in%20a%20now%20forgotten%20but%20critical%20book%20written%20nearly%20forty%20years%20ago.%20In%201985%2C%20veteran%20Punjabi%20politician%2C%20Hanif%20Ramay%2C%20wrote%20a%20book%20called%20%3Cem%3EPunjab%20ka%20Muqadama%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Punjab%E2%80%99s%20Lawsuit).%20Ramay%20dedicated%20his%20book%20to%20the%20then%20%E2%80%98five%20crore%E2%80%99%20Punjabis%20in%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20lamented%20that%20he%20had%20to%20write%20the%20case%20for%20Punjabi%20in%20Urdu%20because%2C%20%E2%80%98the%20Punjabis%20have%20discarded%20the%20Punjabi%20language.%E2%80%99%20He%20explained%20that%20in%20order%20to%20become%20%E2%80%98Pakistani%E2%80%99%20the%20Punjabis%20have%20lost%20their%20language%2C%20culture%20and%20tradition.%20The%20%E2%80%98Speak%20Urdu%2C%20Read%20Urdu%2C%20and%20Write%20Urdu%2C%E2%80%99%20mantra%20of%20the%20Pakistani%20state%20did%20make%20Urdu%20the%20lingua%20franca%20of%20the%20country%20after%20creation%2C%20but%20in%20doing%20so%20destroyed%20the%20Punjabi%20language.%20Ramay%20laments%20that%20the%20%E2%80%98greats%E2%80%99%20of%20Punjabi%20literature%2C%20Waris%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EHeer%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Maulvi%20Ghulam%20Rasool%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EYousaf%20Zuleikha%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20Mian%20Muhammad%20Bakhsh%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ESaif%20ul-Mulook%2C%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3Eare%20now%20hardly%20understood%20by%20the%20Punjabis.%20He%20fears%20that%20with%20the%20language%2C%20the%20dance%2C%20food%2C%20clothes%2C%20arts%20and%20crafts%20of%20the%20Punjab%20are%20also%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20extinction.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20other%20provinces%20did%20not%20wear%20the%20Kurta%2C%20even%20that%20would%20have%20died%20out%20in%20the%20Punjab%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20laments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECertainly%2C%20the%20homogenizing%20tendencies%20of%20the%20early%20Pakistani%20state%20demanded%20that%20Urdu%20and%20north%20Indian%20Muslim%20elite%20(ashraf)%20culture%20held%20prominence%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20Pakistani%20%E2%80%98nation%E2%80%99%20it%20was%20claimed%20should%20only%20have%20%E2%80%98one%E2%80%99%20language%2C%20which%2C%20of%20course%2C%20was%20to%20be%20Urdu.%20The%20founder%20of%20the%20country%2C%20Quaid-e-Azam%20Mohammad%20Ali%20Jinnah%2C%20declared%20the%20hallowed%20status%20of%20Urdu%20as%20early%20as%20March%201948%20in%20Dhaka%20where%20he%20declared%20that%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6let%20me%20make%20it%20very%20clear%20to%20you%20that%20the%20State%20Language%20of%20Pakistan%20is%20going%20to%20be%20Urdu%20and%20no%20other%20language.%20Any%20one%20who%20tries%20to%20mislead%20you%20is%20really%20the%20enemy%20of%20Pakistan.%20Without%20one%20State%20language%2C%20no%20nation%20can%20remain%20tied%20up%20solidly%20together%20and%20function%E2%80%A6Therefore%2C%20so%20far%20as%20the%20State%20Language%20is%20concerned%2C%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20language%20shall%20be%20Urdu.%E2%80%9D%20The%20irony%20was%20certainly%20lost%20that%20this%20speech%20advocating%20for%20Urdu%20was%20given%20in%20English%20and%20by%20a%20person%20who%20was%20himself%20not%20proficient%20in%20the%20Urdu%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20Liaquat%20Ali%20Khan%2C%20saw%20the%20status%20of%20Urdu%20as%20so%20above%20every%20other%20language%2C%20that%20even%20the%20thought%20of%20any%20language%20even%20being%20%E2%80%98co-equal%E2%80%99%20to%20it%20was%20anathema%20to%20him.%20Speaking%20at%20the%20first%20session%20of%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20Pakistan%20in%20February%201948%2C%20where%20an%20East%20Bengal%20member%20merely%20requested%20that%20Bengali%20be%20allowed%20to%20be%20spoken%2C%20together%20with%20English%20and%20Urdu%20in%20the%20Assembly%2C%20Liaquat%20made%20opposition%20to%20this%20suggestion%20a%20matter%20of%20life%20and%20death%E2%80%94not%20just%20for%20Pakistan%20but%20of%20Muslim%20life%20and%20culture%20in%20all%20of%20South%20Asia.%20Liaquat%20retorted%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20really%20the%20most%20vital%20question%2C%20a%20question%20of%20life%20and%20death%20for%20the%20Muslim%20nation%20not%20only%20for%20Pakistan%20but%20throughout%20this%20whole%20sub-continent%20that%20I%20most%20strongly%20oppose%20the%20amendment%20which%20has%20been%20moved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20if%20Urdu%20were%20to%20become%20the%20most%20important%20language%20in%20the%20country%2C%20it%20had%20to%20become%20the%20language%20of%20its%20ruling%20classes%2C%20and%20those%20who%20aspired%20to%20rise%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20polity.%20With%20less%20than%2010%25%20of%20the%20population%20speaking%20Urdu%20as%20a%20first%20language%2C%20but%20with%20a%20large%20number%20of%20influential%20politicians%20and%20bureaucrats%20speaking%20it%20as%20a%20first%20language%2C%20Urdu%20fast%20became%20a%20language%20of%20power%20and%20upward%20mobility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhere%20the%20Bengali%20Pakistanis%20were%20too%20proud%20of%20their%20language%20and%20tradition%20to%20accept%20the%20pre-eminence%20of%20Urdu%2C%20and%20even%20gave%20up%20their%20lives%20in%20February%201952%20in%20order%20to%20achieve%20parity%20with%20it%2C%20the%20Punjabis%20were%20quick%20to%20discard%20their%20language%20and%20culture%20in%20order%20to%20become%20the%20predominant%20power%20in%20western%20Pakistan.%20But%20this%20love%20affair%20with%20Urdu%20had%20historical%20roots%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15181013%2FPunjabi_prachar_demand.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15181013%2FPunjabi_prachar_demand.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15181013%2FPunjabi_prachar_demand-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15181013%2FPunjabi_prachar_demand-1024x768.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-701838%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20demonstration%20by%20Punjabis%20at%20Lahore%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20demanding%20to%20make%20Punjabi%20as%20official%20language%20of%20instruction%20in%20schools%20of%20the%20Punjab.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FPunjabi%20parchar%2FCC%20BY-SA%204.0%20DEED%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHistorical%20injustice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUrdu%2C%20like%20English%2C%20was%20brought%20to%20the%20Punjab%20formally%20by%20the%20British%20in%201849%20with%20annexation.%20Not%20only%20were%20the%20lower%20level%20bureaucrats%20in%20the%20government%20Urdu%20speaking%2C%20as%20they%20hailed%20from%20the%20then%20North-Western%20provinces%2C%20the%20British%20had%20a%20particular%20affinity%20for%20Urdu%2C%20treating%20it%20as%20their%20%E2%80%98own%E2%80%99%20language%2C%20as%20they%20had%20played%20a%20large%20part%20in%20popularising%20it.%20Urdu%20also%20played%20a%20major%20role%20in%20the%20Punjab%20as%20it%20was%20used%20by%20the%20British%20to%20replace%20Persian.%20Liberal%20scholarships%20were%20given%20for%20the%20study%20of%20Urdu%20by%20the%20British%2C%20while%20Persian%20was%20discouraged%2C%20so%20much%20so%20that%20by%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20twentieth%20century%20the%20Punjab%20education%20department%20gleefully%20noted%20that%20Persian%20had%20almost%20died%20out%20in%20the%20province.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20when%20Pakistan%20came%20into%20being%20and%20Urdu%20became%20even%20more%20important%20as%20the%20upcoming%20language%20of%20state%2C%20the%20Punjabis%2C%20where%20already%20the%20educated%20classes%20knew%20Urdu%2C%20were%20quick%20to%20take%20up%20the%20mantle%20of%20being%20the%20leaders%20in%20forging%20the%20identity%20of%20this%20new%20country%20through%20religion%20and%20language.%20There%20was%20one%20further%20measure%20too%3A%20Punjabi%20was%20now%20seen%20as%20only%20rustic%2C%20only%20to%20be%20spoken%2C%20and%20never%20to%20be%20written%2C%20nor%20to%20be%20taught%20or%20used%20academically.%20This%20denigration%20of%20Punjabi%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98paindoo%E2%80%99%20(village)%20language%20meant%20that%20people%20began%20to%20connect%20it%20to%20being%20uneducated%2C%20backward%2C%20and%20even%20uncouth.%20Henceforth%2C%20while%20still%20spoken%2C%20Punjabi%20almost%20disappeared%20from%20schools%20in%20the%20province%2C%20and%20only%20became%20the%20preserve%20of%20a%20few%20small%20postgraduate%20university%20departments.%20Today%20only%20one%20private%20school%20in%20Lahore%20regularly%20teaches%20Punjabi%2C%20and%20no%20university%20offers%20it%20as%20a%20regular%20course%20to%20its%20undergraduates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20began%20going%20to%20Indian%20Punjab%20regularly%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20I%20frequently%20visited%20the%20Panjab%20University%20and%20the%20Punjabi%20University.%20The%20former%20claims%20that%20it%20is%20the%20successor%20of%20the%20University%20of%20the%20Punjab%20established%20at%20Lahore%20in%201882%2C%20while%20the%20later%20was%20established%20in%201962%20as%20the%20first%20Punjabi%20medium%20university%20in%20India.%20My%20first%20visit%20to%20both%20these%20universities%20in%202013%20left%20me%20speechless.%20At%20the%20conference%20I%20was%20invited%20to%20at%20Panjab%20University%20in%20Chandigarh%20the%20then%20Vice%20Chancellor%2C%20Professor%20Arun%20Grover%2C%20a%20distinguished%20scientist%2C%20started%20the%20proceedings%20in%20Punjabi%2C%20and%20encouraged%20discourse%20in%20the%20language%20at%20the%20conference.%20The%20subsequent%20conference%20at%20Punjabi%20University%20Patiala%20simply%20had%20Punjabi%20as%20its%20main%20medium%2C%20with%20every%20single%20person%20speaking%20the%20language%20academically%20as%20well%20as%20colloquially.%20Such%20ease%20with%20Punjabi%20in%20educational%20institutions%20is%20simply%20unimaginable%20in%20Pakistani%20Punjab%20still%2C%20and%20its%20absence%20creates%20a%20gaping%20hole%20not%20only%20in%20the%20educational%20milieu%20of%20the%20province%2C%20but%20also%20the%20identity%20of%20Pakistani%20Punjabis%2C%20which%20is%20simply%20incomplete%20without%20learning%2C%20owning%20and%20being%20proud%20of%20its%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHanif%20Ramay%20died%20in%202006%20with%20an%20unfulfilled%20dream.%20In%202024%2C%20its%20seems%20that%20it%20is%20in%20the%20lot%20of%20Maryam%20Nawaz%20Sharif%20to%20correct%20this%20historical%20wrong%2C%20and%20reintroduce%20Punjabi%20to%20its%20homeland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EYaqoob%20Khan%20Bangash%20is%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Ea%20historian%20based%20in%20Lahore%2C%20Pakistan.%20Bangsh%20tweets%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBangashYK%5C%22%3E%40BangashYK%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20can%20be%20reached%20at%20yaqoob.bangash%40gmail.com.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710511168000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15180250%2FUntitled-design-43.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpunjabi-in-pakistan-schools-can-the-latest-move-undo-injustice-done-to-the-language%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Maryam%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%20the%20first%20woman%20chief%20minister%20of%20Pakistani%20Punjab%2C%20recently%20announced%20that%20Punjabi%20will%20be%20taught%20in%20all%20schools%20across%20province.%20The%20decision%20is%20being%20hailed%20as%20'historic'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fpunjabi-in-pakistan-schools-can-the-latest-move-undo-injustice-done-to-the-language%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Barred%20opposition%20candidate%20says%20not%20crossing%20Russia's%20'red%20lines'%20has%20kept%20him%20out%20of%20prison%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710511080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F03%2F768x432%2Fskynews-boris-nadezhdin-russia_6491282.jpg%3F20240315144007%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Frussia-election-2024-barred-opposition-candidate-says-not-crossing-red-lines-has-kept-him-out-of-prison-13095312%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20Russian%20opposition%20politician%20who%20was%20barred%20from%20running%20in%20the%20presidential%20election%20has%20told%20Sky%20News%20he%20will%20not%20meet%20the%20same%20fate%20as%20Alexei%20Navalny%20because%20he%20does%20not%20cross%20political%20%26quot%3Bred%20lines%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A116%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Frussia-election-2024-barred-opposition-candidate-says-not-crossing-red-lines-h