20care%3A%20gender%20and%20the%20undervaluation%20of%20health%20and%20care%20work%2C%E2%80%99%20the%20report%20said%20that%20women%20constitute%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20global%20health%20and%20care%20workforce%2C%20yet%20they%20also%20perform%20the%20majority%20of%20unpaid%20care%20activities.%20This%20imbalance%20results%20in%20lower%20wages%20and%20poor%20working%20conditions%20for%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWomen%20comprise%2067%25%20of%20the%20paid%20global%20health%20and%20care%20workforce.%20In%20addition%20to%20this%20paid%20work%2C%20it%20has%20been%20estimated%20that%20women%20perform%20an%20estimated%2076%25%20of%20all%20unpaid%20care%20activities.%20Work%20that%20is%20done%20primarily%20by%20women%20tends%20to%20be%20paid%20less%20and%20have%20poor%20working%20conditions%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20highlights%20that%20low%20pay%20and%20demanding%20working%20conditions%20are%20commonly%20found%20in%20the%20health%20and%20care%20sector.%20Devaluing%20caregiving%2C%20which%20is%20work%20performed%20primarily%20by%20women%2C%20negatively%20impacts%20wages%2C%20working%20conditions%2C%20productivity%20and%20the%20economic%20footprint%20of%20the%20sector%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChronic%20underinvestment%20in%20health%20and%20care%20exacerbates%20this%20issue%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20global%20crisis%20of%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20stagnation%20in%20progress%20towards%20universal%20health%20coverage%2C%20resulting%20in%204.5%20billion%20people%20lacking%20full%20coverage%20of%20essential%20health%20services%2C%20women%20may%20take%20on%20even%20more%20unpaid%20care%20work.%20The%20deleterious%20impact%20of%20weak%20health%20systems%20combined%20with%20increasing%20unpaid%20health%20and%20care%20work%20are%20further%20straining%20the%20health%20of%20caregivers%20and%20the%20quality%20of%20services%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20%E2%80%98Fair%20share%E2%80%99%20report%20highlights%20how%20gender-equitable%20investments%20in%20health%20and%20care%20work%20would%20reset%20the%20value%20of%20health%20and%20care%20and%20drive%20fairer%20and%20more%20inclusive%20economies%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Jim%20Campbell%2C%20WHO%20director%20for%20Health%20Workforce.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20calling%20upon%20leaders%2C%20policymakers%20and%20employers%20to%20action%20investment%3A%20it%20is%20time%20for%20a%20fair%20share%20for%20health%20and%20care.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20calls%20for%20gender-equitable%20investments%20and%20policy%20measures%20to%20value%20and%20support%20health%20and%20care%20work%2C%20stressing%20the%20importance%20of%20recognising%20and%20investing%20in%20robust%20public%20health%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710509420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2F15181020%2Fimage-1962.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fglobally-women-perform-76-of-all-unpaid-activities-in-health-and-care-sector-who-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20highlights%20that%20low%20pay%20and%20demanding%20working%20conditions%20are%20commonly%20found%20in%20the%20health%20and%20care%20sector.%20And%20chronic%20underinvestment%20in%20health%20and%20care%20exacerbates%20this%20issue%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20global%20crisis%20of%20care.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwomen%2Fglobally-women-perform-76-of-all-unpaid-activities-in-health-and-care-sector-who-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Navayuga%20Engineering%20Responsible%20for%20Building%20the%20Collapsed%20Silkyara%20Tunnel%20Bought%20Rs%2055%20Cr%20of%20Bonds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01140335%2FGACaXNpbYAASMBx.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20De